body:
This last game, I noticed my teammates were all attacking the enemy tank because, of course, the enemy tank led the charge. I said in chat "guys, get the adc first". One of my teammates started the rant of "don&#039;t tell me what to do", bla bla bla, "I'll just sit top" bla bla bla. I said, "if we don&#039;t focus the adc, we will lose" and the reply was something along the lines of "I would rather lose than obey a tyrant".

What...? This person must have been 12 years old or something and have parents that don&#039;t ever make them do ANYTHING. Any adult who has had ONE job has been told what to do. Me suggesting obvious strategies to win is me being a tyrant? This isn&#039;t even about pride anymore; this is just plain stupidity.

We did lose; so, he really showed me. {{summoner:14}}
